title: Princess Kate’s diagnosis reflects growing number of cancer cases among young people
description: Princess Kate revealed she is undergoing preventative chemo treatments after cancer was discovered after her January abdominal surgery. The announcement comes as cancer diagnoses are on the rise among people under 50. NBC News’ Meagan Fitzgerald reports.

title: Death toll rises and new details emerge from Moscow concert hall terror attack
description: At least 133 people were killed and hundreds injured in the terror attack on a Moscow concert hall Friday night. ISIS-Khorasan has claimed responsibility as 11 people have been arrested, including four who participated directly in the attack. NBC News’ Matt Bradley reports.

title: A method being weighed for distributing U.S. aid in Gaza could put U.S. troops at risk, officials say
description: The Biden admin doesn't want U.S. troops to set foot in Gaza when it starts delivering humanitarian aid from a floating dock, but an alternate plan poses risks.

title: Putin vows to punish perpetrators after deadly Moscow concert attack
description: Russian President Vladimir Putin addressed Russia after gunmen carried out a deadly attack on a crowded concert venue in Moscow. Putin vowed that the perpetrators would be "rightfully and inevitably punished."

title: Camembert cheese faces potential threats in production
description: Camembert cheese may potentiality become difficult to produce in the future as the fungus used to get its smell and taste is losing its ability to reproduce. NBC News' Josh Lederman breaks down the history of the cheese and how it's made.

title: Hong Kong passes new controversial national security law
description: Hong Kong has passed a new national security law called Article 23, which covers acts of treason, subversion, and foreign interference. The article expands on a national security law imposed by China in 2020.
